President Donald J. Trump has nominated Derek Kan to serve as the Under Secretary of Transportation for Policy at the Department of Transportation. Kan is currently the General Manager for Lyft in Southern California and has also served on the Board of Amtrak since 2015. He has previous experience as the Director of Strategy at a startup in Silicon Valley, as a management consultant at Bain & Company, as a policy advisor to Senate Republican Leader Mitch McConnell, and as the chief economist for the Senate Republican Policy Committee. Kan has also worked as a Presidential Management Fellow at the White House Office of Management and Budget. He holds a B.S. from the University of Southern California, an M.Sc. from the London School of Economics, and an M.B.A. from the Stanford Graduate School of Business. Kan resides in San Gabriel, California with his wife and three children.